-- Exxon says will ensure supply after cutoff
-- 
-- Tue Feb 12, 2008 8:00pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/02/13/us-exxon-venezuela-statement-idUSN1229288020080213

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Exxon Mobil Corp ( XOM.N ) on Tuesday said it will take steps to ensure supply after Venezuela cut off crude exports to the company. 

 "It is our longstanding practice to take appropriate steps to meet our customer needs," spokeswoman Margaret Ross said. (Reporting by  Michael Erman ; Editing by  David Gregorio )